what are Services?
 - Services are a local set of pods through which you can access them. It enables you to coupling between pods, making it easier to manage.
 - Services Uses Selectors 
      Selectors - These are used to define which pods the service targets. This is a type of label that is attached to the pods
Types of services:-
  1. Load Balancer - Expose to the cloud provider(like EC2). It creates an inflow of external traffic
  2. Node port - Expose service on each node IP at a static point.
  3. Cluster IP (Default) - Using this service you expose your cluster to the internal IP.



